<TITLE> Carjackers shoot driver to minister's aide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 12 (bdnews24.com)Carjackers shot 30 year-old Kabir Hossain, driver to the private secretary of the state minister for local government, before making off with the government car late Saturday night. Hossain was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital on Sunday morning after being given emergency treatment at a Savar hospital. He told bdnews24.com from his hospital bed that he drove his boss Matiur Rahman to minister Jahangir Kabir Nanak's Uttara home late Saturday night. On his way back four gunmen held up the car before he could reach the main Airport Road. "I was thrown in the back seat. They shot me in the left leg and left hand and then dumped me at Savar before speeding away," said Hossain. Locals found him and took him to the Enam Medical Hospital in Savar. Uttara police officer-in-charge Zakir Hossain told bdnews24.com they were gathering information. He added that it was an official car and Hossain was a government driver. b
